Director
(d)        .  The Participant shall be considered to have a "Disability" during the period in which the Participant is unable, by reason of a medically determinable physical or mental impairment, to engage in any substantial gainful activity, which condition, in the opinion of a physician selected by the Committee, is expected to have a duration of not less than 120 days.
Disability
(e)        .  "Retirement" of a Participant shall mean with respect to an employee of the Company or a Subsidiary, the occurrence of a Participant's Date of Termination with the consent of the Participant's employer after the Participant is eligible for early retirement or normal retirement under the ACE Limited Employee Retirement Plan (or any other retirement plan maintained by the Company or the Subsidiaries) and with respect to a Director, the Participant's Date of Termination with the consent of the Company after the Participant would be eligible for retirement under any retirement plan maintained by the Company or a Subsidiary if the Director were an employee of the Company or a Subsidiary; provided, however, that the Committee may impose such additional or alternative conditions or restrictions on Retirement as it determines to be appropriate.
