Exhibit 99.1
 
 
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
 
 
 
 August 14, 2007  ACE Limited (NYSE: ACE) announced today that Leo F. Mullin has been elected to its Board of Directors, effective immediately.
HAMILTON, Bermuda
 
Between 1997 and 2004 Mr. Mullin was associated with Delta Air Lines where he was separately and concurrently Chairman, President and Chief Executive Officer. From 1995 to 1997 Mr. Mullin held the position of Vice Chairman of Unicom Corporation. Previously, Mr. Mullin served as President and Chief Operating Officer of First National Bank of Chicago and he has held senior positions with Consolidated Rail Corp. and McKinsey & Company. Since 2004, Mr. Mullin has served on a part time basis as a senior advisor to Goldman Sachs Capital Partners.
 
Mr. Mullin also currently serves as a director of Johnson & Johnson.
 
Evan Greenberg, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of ACE Limited, stated: "We are honored to welcome Leo Mullin to the Board of Directors of ACE. Leo has a broad and impressive record of accomplishment in the banking, transportation and energy industries. I'm confident given his deep knowledge and experience that Leo will make a significant contribution toward the governance of ACE."
 
