Check the appropriate box below if the Form 8-K filing is intended to simultaneously satisfy the filing obligation of the registrant under any of the following provisions (General Instruction A.2. below):
see
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
On January 30, 2008, the Company amended its outsourcing agreement with International Business Machines Corporation relating to the management of the Company's information technology infrastructure. The amendment extended the term of the outsourcing agreement for an additional two years so that the agreement will be in effect until 2014 and reduced the projected payments from the Company per year by an estimated $7 million. Additionally, the amendment does not allow for the Company to invoke its right to terminate the agreement for convenience and without cause until after December 31, 2009. Finally, the amendment permits IBM to provide some services from locations outside the United States after obtaining the Company's prior written consent. The amendment is effective as of January 1, 2008.
Pursuant to the requirements of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, the Registrant has duly caused this report to be signed on its behalf by the undersigned thereunto duly authorized.
 
DATE: February 5, 2008


