(a) At the company's 2008 annual general meeting, the company's shareholders approved payments of a dividend in the form of a par value reduction equal to CHF 0.90 in the aggregate (equivalent at the time to US$0.87), to be paid in three equal quarterly installments (each equivalent at the time to US$0.29), as further described in the company's proxy statement/prospectus dated May 30, 2008. To accomplish this par value reduction for the fourth quarter of 2008, the company adjusted its Articles of Association on December 16, 2008 to reflect the number of shares issued out of conditional share capital since September 30, 2008 and on December 17, 2008 to confirm the par value reduction. The company's amended and restated Articles of Association became effective upon their filing with the commercial register of the Canton of Zurich, Switzerland on December 17, 2008 and as a result, the company's par value is now CHF 33.14 per share. Accordingly, the dividend will be paid to the company's shareholders of record at the close of business on December 17, 2008, as anticipated. A copy of the amended and restated Articles of Association is attached hereto as Exhibit 3 and incorporated herein by reference.
 
