Combined Insurance Company of America, acquired April 1, 2008.
Combined Insurance:
 
The sum of the loss and loss expense ratio, acquisition cost ratio and the administrative expense ratio excluding life business. Calculated on a GAAP basis.
Combined ratio:
 
Shareholders' equity less perpetual preferred shares.
Common shareholders' equity:
 
Income tax expense divided by the sum of income tax expense and income excluding net realized gains (losses).
Effective tax rate:
 
Unrealized gains (losses) on investments and the deferred tax component included in shareholders' equity.
FAS 115:
 
A group of seven industrialized nations including Canada, France, Germany, Italy, Japan, United Kingdom, and the United States.
G7:
 
Net premiums earned and net investment income less policy benefits, acquisition costs, and administrative expenses.
Life underwriting income:
 
Not meaningful.
NM:
 
Common shareholders' equity less goodwill and other intangible assets divided by the shares outstanding.
